---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import DocSidebar from '../../components/DocSidebar.astro';
import DocContent from '../../components/DocContent.astro';

const title = 'Configuration';
const currentPage = '/docs/configuration';

const content = `
<h2>Two-Tier Configuration</h2>
<p>VibePrint OS uses a two-tier configuration system:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Environment variables</strong> (<code>.env</code> file) — Infrastructure settings like secrets, database URLs, and hardware detection. Set before deployment, require restart to apply.</li>
  <li><strong>Admin panel</strong> (<code>/admin</code> in the UI) — Runtime settings like AI provider, pricing, templates, and access codes. Changes take effect immediately without restart.</li>
</ol>
<p>On first startup, runtime settings are seeded from env var defaults into the database. After that, operators change them via the admin panel — no redeployment needed.</p>

<h2>Environment Variables</h2>
<p>Copy <code>.env.example</code> (development) or <code>.env.production</code> (production) to <code>.env</code> and fill in the values.</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>APP_ENV</code></td><td><code>development</code></td><td><code>development</code> or <code>production</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>APP_SECRET_KEY</code></td><td><code>change-me-in-production</code></td><td>JWT signing key — generate with <code>python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>APP_DEBUG</code></td><td><code>true</code></td><td>Enables detailed error traces. Always <code>false</code> in production.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>LOG_LEVEL</code></td><td><code>INFO</code></td><td>Application log level: <code>DEBUG</code>, <code>INFO</code>, <code>WARNING</code>, <code>ERROR</code>, <code>CRITICAL</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>DATABASE_URL</code></td><td><code>postgresql+asyncpg://...</code></td><td>PostgreSQL connection string (async driver required)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>ADMIN_PIN</code></td><td><code>1234</code></td><td>PIN for admin dashboard access</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>CAMERA_DEVICE_INDEX</code></td><td><code>0</code></td><td>Camera device index (<code>/dev/video0</code> = 0)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS</code></td><td><code>http://localhost:5173,...</code></td><td>Comma-separated allowed origins (dev only)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Admin Panel Settings (Runtime)</h2>
<p>These are configured via the admin dashboard at <code>/admin</code> after deployment — no <code>.env</code> edits needed:</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Category</th><th>Settings</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>AI</td><td>Provider (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Ollama, Mock), API keys, model, system prompt, timeout</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Payment</td><td>Enable/disable, provider (Midtrans/Xendit/Mock), amount, currency, timeout</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Printer Hardware</td><td>USB vendor/product ID, paper width</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Camera</td><td>Resolution</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Photobooth</td><td>Enable, capture time, min/max photos, layout, watermark, retention</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Vibe Check</td><td>Enable, system prompt, retention</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Kiosk UX</td><td>Idle timeout, countdown, processing timeout, reveal duration</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Print Template</td><td>Footer brand name, timezone, per-element toggles</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Access Codes</td><td>Enable/disable access code mode, batch generation, expiry, QR codes, revocation</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>AI Provider Fallback</h2>
<p>When the primary AI provider fails (rate limit, network error, invalid key), VibePrint OS automatically falls back through the provider chain so the kiosk keeps running. Check the admin dashboard logs to see fallback events.</p>

<h2>Payment Toggle</h2>
<p>Payment is disabled by default. Enable it via the admin panel and configure your provider (Midtrans or Xendit) with production keys. The mock provider simulates successful payments for development and testing.</p>
`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Configuration — VibePrint OS Docs">
  <div style="max-width: 72rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div class="doc-layout" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column;">
      <DocSidebar currentPage={currentPage} />
      <DocContent title={title} content={content} currentPage={currentPage} />
    </div>
  </div>
  <style>
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .doc-layout { flex-direction: row !important; }
  }
</style>
</BaseLayout>
